Title : Bruce DeSilva
Text : '''Bruce DeSilva''' (born in [[Taunton, Massachusetts]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Bruce DeSilva, Author of Rogue Island|url=http://www.goodreads.com/author/show/524126.Bruce_DeSilva|publisher=GoodReads|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref>) is an American author and journalist. 

== Career ==
DeSilva was a [[Journalism|journalist]] for forty years, and has reviewed books for ''[[The New York Times]]''. 

As an author, DeSilva is best known for the ''Liam Mulligan'' series of [[Mystery fiction|mystery]] novels, including ''Rogue Island'', ''Cliff Walk'', ''Providence Rag'', ''A Scourge of Vipers'' and ''The Dread Line''. His novels won him the [[Edgar Award|Edgar]] & [[Macavity Award]]s.

== Personal life ==
DeSilva is married to [[Patricia Smith (poet)|Patricia Smith]], a poet. DeSilva lives in New Jersey.<ref>{{cite web |URL=https://www.nyjournalofbooks.com/reviewer/bruce-desilva |title=Bruce DeSilva |publisher=nyjournalofbooks.com |accessdate=February 3, 2019}}</ref>

